  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-05 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). This package contains a targeted W-AR-05 defeater: the primary validation result omits a comparedAgainst link, while the comparator referenced in narrative text is drawn from ventricular-assist-device (VAD) bench data operating at 5 L/min / 3500 RPM — conditions that overlap the CPB envelope on flow rate but differ substantially on rotational speed and pressure head, parameters that govern shear-stress magnitude and therefore hemolysis index. The mismatch is presented in positive terms without scrutiny of COU applicability.",
