      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/no-comparator",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Primary hemolysis QoI validation — CPB operating envelope",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values were computed across all five CPB operating points (2.5–5.0 L/min, 2000–3000 RPM) and evaluated against experimentally measured hemolysis data. The experimental reference dataset from Graefe et al. (2022) provides in-vitro hemolysis measurements for a geometrically similar centrifugal pump platform and is considered a high-quality benchmark by the assessment team. Agreement between CFD and experiment was assessed using the relative hemolysis index RH, with all five operating points yielding RH < 1.0 against the Graefe dataset. The Graefe measurements were conducted on a magnetically levitated centrifugal pump of comparable impeller diameter and volute geometry, and the dataset is widely cited in the rotary blood pump literature. On this basis the validation activity is judged to demonstrate adequate predictive capability for the declared COU. No further comparator qualification was deemed necessary.",
      "quantityOfInterest": "Normalized Index of Hemolysis (NIH), g/100 L",
      "acceptanceCriterion": "RH < 1.0 for all five CPB operating points",
      "outcomeStatement": "All five operating points satisfy RH < 1.0; validation activity assessed as passed.",
